        <mainBody xml:id="_body">
            <paragraph xml:id="_body__unnumpara_1">
                <content xml:id="_body__unnumpara_1__content">
                    <p xml:id="_body__unnumpara_1__content__p">
                        <i xml:id="_body__unnumpara_1__content__p_i_1">Guidance  for scenario 1: (Coreper-level) mandate for negotiations with the European Parliament (I item note)</i>
                    </p>
                </content>
            </paragraph>
            <division xml:id="_body_division_1" class="type_1">
                <num xml:id="_body_division_1_num"><b>I.</b></num>
                <heading xml:id="_body_division_1_heading"><b>BACKGROUND/INTRODUCTION</b></heading>
            </division>
            <level xml:id="_body_level_1" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_1_num">1.</num>
                <content xml:id="_body_level_1_content">
                    <p xml:id="_body_level_1_content_p">On …, the <u xml:id="_body_level_1__content__p_u_1">Commission</u> submitted
                        to the Council and the European Parliament a proposal for a Regulation/Directive/Decision of the European
                        Parliament and of the Council …<authorialNote xml:id="_authorialnote_1" marker="1" placement="bottom">
                            <p>12345/21.</p>
                        </authorialNote>, which aims to …
                    </p>
                </content>
            </level>
            <level xml:id="_body_level_2" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_2_num">2.</num>
                <content xml:id="_body_level_2_content">
                    <p xml:id="_body_level_2_content_p">The draft Regulation/Directive/Decision is based on Article … of the Treaty on the
                        Functioning of the European Union (TFEU) (ordinary legislative procedure).
                    </p>
                </content>
            </level>
            <level xml:id="_body_level_3" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_3_num">3.</num>
                <content xml:id="_body_level_3_content">
                    <p xml:id="_body_level_3_content_p"><i xml:id="_body_level_3__content__p_i_1">(where applicable)</i> The <u xml:id="_body_level_3__content__p_u_1">XXX</u> delivered its opinion on …<authorialNote xml:id="_authorialnote_2" marker="2" placement="bottom">
                            <p>Not yet published in the Official Journal.</p>
                        </authorialNote>. / decided not to deliver an opinion on the proposal. / The opinion of <u xml:id="_body_level_3__content__p_u_2">XXX</u> was requested on … (and is pending).
                    </p>
                </content>
            </level>
            <level xml:id="_body_level_4" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_4_num">4.</num>
                <content xml:id="_body_level_4_content">
                    <p xml:id="_body_level_4_content_p">The [<u xml:id="_body_level_4__content__p_u_1">name of the Council preparatory body</u>] discussed the proposal at its meetings on [dates] and has agreed on the text in the annex/annexes (or in addendum/addenda XX) to this note.
                    </p>
                </content>
            </level>
            <level xml:id="_body_level_5" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_5_num">5.</num>
                <content xml:id="_body_level_5_content">
                    <p xml:id="_body_level_5_content_p">In the <u xml:id="_body_level_5__content__p_u_1">European Parliament</u>,
                        the Committee(s) on … has/have the lead responsibility. … was/were appointed rapporteur(s). The report was tabled on …;
                        [the negotiating mandate was granted at the plenary session on … to start interinstitutional negotiations.] / [the
                        <u xml:id="_body_level_5__content__p_u_2">European Parliament</u> adopted its negotiating mandate at the plenary session on …,
                        and the proposal was referred to the Committee(s) on … to start interinstitutional negotiations].
                    </p>
                </content>
            </level>
            <division xml:id="_body_division_2" class="type_1">
                <num xml:id="_body_division_2_num"><b>II.</b></num>
                <heading xml:id="_body_division_2_heading"><b>CONCLUSION</b></heading>
            </division>
            <level xml:id="_body_level_6" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_6_num">6.</num>
                <content xml:id="_body_level_6_content">
                    <p xml:id="_body_level_6_content_p">The <u xml:id="_body_level_6__content__p_u_1">Permanent Representatives Committee</u>
                        is therefore invited to confirm agreement on the text of the mandate for negotiations with the European Parliament,
                        as set out in the annex/annexes (or in addendum/addenda XX) to this note, to enable the Presidency to conduct those negotiations.
                    </p>
                </content>
            </level>
            <level xml:id="_body_level_7" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_7_num">7.</num>
                <content xml:id="_body_level_7_content">
                    <p xml:id="_body_level_7_content_p">In accordance with the approach to legislative transparency endorsed by Coreper on 14 July 2020<authorialNote xml:id="_authorialnote_3" marker="3" placement="bottom">
                            <p>9493/20.</p>
                        </authorialNote>, and in full consistency with Regulation 1049/2001 and the Council's Rules of Procedure, the mandate thus agreed will be made public unless the Permanent Representatives Committee objects.
                    </p>
                </content>
            </level>
            <paragraph xml:id="_body__unnumpara_2">
                <content xml:id="_body__unnumpara_2__content">
                    <p xml:id="_body__unnumpara_2__content__p">
                        <i xml:id="_body__unnumpara_2__content__p_i_1">Guidance  for scenario 2: (Council-level) general approach – I/A or A item note</i>
                    </p>
                </content>
            </paragraph>
            <division xml:id="_body_division_3" class="type_1">
                <num xml:id="_body_division_3_num"><b>III.</b></num>
                <heading xml:id="_body_division_3_heading"><b>BACKGROUND/INTRODUCTION</b></heading>
            </division>
            <level xml:id="_body_level_8" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_8_num">8.</num>
                <content xml:id="_body_level_8_content">
                    <p xml:id="_body_level_8_content_p">On …, the <u xml:id="_body_level_8__content__p_u_1">Commission</u> submitted to the Council and the
                        European Parliament a proposal for a Regulation/Directive/Decision of the European Parliament and of the Council …<authorialNote xml:id="_authorialnote_4" marker="4" placement="bottom">
                            <p>12345/21.</p>
                        </authorialNote>, which aims to …
                    </p>
                </content>
            </level>
            <level xml:id="_body_level_9" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_9_num">9.</num>
                <content xml:id="_body_level_9_content">
                    <p xml:id="_body_level_9_content_p">The draft Regulation/Directive/Decision is based on Article … of the Treaty on the Functioning of the
                        European Union (TFEU) (ordinary legislative procedure).
                    </p>
                </content>
            </level>
            <level xml:id="_body_level_10" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_10_num">10.</num>
                <content xml:id="_body_level_10_content">
                    <p xml:id="_body_level_10_content_p"><i xml:id="_body_level_10__content__p_i_1">(where applicable)</i> The <u xml:id="_body_level_10__content__p_u_1">XXX</u> delivered its opinion on …<authorialNote xml:id="_authorialnote_5" marker="5" placement="bottom">
                            <p>Not yet published in the Official Journal.</p>
                        </authorialNote>. / decided not to deliver an opinion on the proposal. / The opinion of <u xml:id="_body_level_10__content__p_u_2">XXX</u> was requested on … (and is pending).
                    </p>
                </content>
            </level>
            <level xml:id="_body_level_11" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_11_num">11.</num>
                <content xml:id="_body_level_11_content">
                    <p xml:id="_body_level_11_content_p">The [<u xml:id="_body_level_11__content__p_u_1">name of the Council preparatory body</u>] discussed the proposal at its meetings on [dates] and has agreed on the text in the annex/annexes (or in addendum/addenda XX) to this note.
                    </p>
                </content>
            </level>
            <level xml:id="_body_level_12" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_12_num">12.</num>
                <content xml:id="_body_level_12_content">
                    <p xml:id="_body_level_12_content_p">In the <u xml:id="_body_level_12__content__p_u_1">European Parliament</u> , the Committee(s) on … has/have the lead responsibility. … was
                        /were appointed rapporteur(s). The report was tabled on …; [the negotiating mandate was granted at the plenary session on … to start interinstitutional negotiations.] / [the
                        <u xml:id="_body_level_12__content__p_u_2">European Parliament</u> adopted its negotiating mandate at the plenary session on …, and the proposal was referred to the
                        Committee(s) on … to start interinstitutional negotiations].
                    </p>
                </content>
            </level>
            <division xml:id="_body_division_4" class="type_1">
                <num xml:id="_body_division_4_num"><b>IV.</b></num>
                <heading xml:id="_body_division_4_heading"><b>CONCLUSION</b></heading>
            </division>
            <paragraph xml:id="_body__unnumpara_3">
                <content xml:id="_body__unnumpara_3__content">
                    <p xml:id="_body__unnumpara_3__content__p">
                        <i xml:id="_body__unnumpara_3__content__p_i_1">In  case of an I/A item in Council</i>
                    </p>
                </content>
            </paragraph>
            <level xml:id="_body_level_13" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_13_num">13.</num>
                <subparagraph xml:id="_body_level_13_subpara_1">
                    <content xml:id="_body_level_13_subpara_1_content">
                        <p xml:id="_body_level_13_content_p">The <u xml:id="_body_level_13_subpara_1_content__p_u_1">Permanent Representatives Committee</u> is therefore invited to:
                        </p>
                    </content>
                </subparagraph>
                <list xml:id="_body_level_13_list_1">
                    <point xml:id="_body_level_13_list_1_point_1">
                        <num xml:id="_body_level_13_list_1_point_1_num">(a)</num>
                        <content xml:id="_body_level_13_list_1_point_1_content">
                            <p xml:id="_body_level_13_list_1_point_1_content_p">confirm agreement on the text of the general approach, as set out in the annex/annexes
                                (or in addendum/addenda XX) to this note, and
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </point>
                    <point xml:id="_body_level_13_list_1_point_2">
                        <num xml:id="_body_level_13_list_1_point_2_num">(b)</num>
                        <content xml:id="_body_level_13_list_1_point_2_content">
                            <p xml:id="_body_level_13_list_1_point_2_content_p">recommend that the <u xml:id="_body_level_13_list_1_point_2_content__p_u_1">Council</u> reach
                                a general approach as set out in the annex/annexes (or in addendum XX) to this note, through an ‘A’ item in one of its next meetings,
                                to enable the Presidency to conduct those negotiations.
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </point>
                </list>
            </level>
            <paragraph xml:id="_body__unnumpara_4">
                <content xml:id="_body__unnumpara_4__content">
                    <p xml:id="_body__unnumpara_4__content__p">
                        <i xml:id="_body__unnumpara_4__content__p_i_1">In  case of an A item</i>
                    </p>
                </content>
            </paragraph>
            <level xml:id="_body_level_14" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_14_num">14.</num>
                <content xml:id="_body_level_14_content">
                    <p xml:id="_body_level_14_content_p">At its meeting on …, the <u xml:id="_body_level_14_content_p_u_1"> Permanent Representatives Committee (Part I/Part II)</u> examined
                        the text set out in the annex/annexes (or in addendum/addenda XX) and agreed to recommend that the Council reach a general approach.
                    </p>
                </content>
            </level>
            <level xml:id="_body_level_15" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_15_num">15.</num>
                <content xml:id="_body_level_15_content">
                    <p xml:id="_body_level_15_content_p">The <u xml:id="_body_level_15_content_p_u_1">Council</u> is therefore invited to reach a general approach as set out in the annex/annexes
                        (or in addendum/addenda XX) to this note.
                    </p>
                </content>
            </level>
            <paragraph xml:id="_body__unnumpara_5">
                <content xml:id="_body__unnumpara_5__content">
                    <p xml:id="_body__unnumpara_5__content__p">
                        <i xml:id="_body__unnumpara_5__content__p_i_1">Guidance  for scenario 3: Confirmation of the final compromise text with a view to agreement at first reading (I item note)</i>
                    </p>
                </content>
            </paragraph>
            <division xml:id="_body_division_5" class="type_1">
                <num xml:id="_body_division_5_num"><b>V.</b></num>
                <heading xml:id="_body_division_5_heading"><b>BACKGROUND/INTRODUCTION</b></heading>
            </division>
            <level xml:id="_body_level_16" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_16_num">16.</num>
                <content xml:id="_body_level_16_content">
                    <p xml:id="_body_level_16_content_p">On …, the <u xml:id="_body_level_16_content_p_u_1">Commission</u> submitted to the Council and the European Parliament a proposal for a Regulation/Directive/Decision
                        of the European Parliament and of the Council …<authorialNote xml:id="_authorialnote_6" marker="6" placement="bottom">
                            <p>12345/21.</p>
                        </authorialNote>, which aims to …
                    </p>
                </content>
            </level>
            <level xml:id="_body_level_17" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_17_num">17.</num>
                <content xml:id="_body_level_17_content">
                    <p xml:id="_body_level_17_content_p">The draft Regulation/Directive/Decision is based on Article … of the Treaty on the Functioning of the European Union (TFEU) (ordinary legislative procedure).
                    </p>
                </content>
            </level>

            <level xml:id="_body_level_18" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_18_num">18.</num>
                <content xml:id="_body_level_18_content">
                    <p xml:id="_body_level_18_content_p"><i xml:id="_body_level_18_content_p_i_1">(where applicable)</i> The <u xml:id="_body_level_18_content_p_u_1">XXX</u> delivered its opinion on …<authorialNote xml:id="_authorialnote_7" marker="7" placement="bottom">
                            <p>Not yet published in the Official Journal.</p>
                        </authorialNote>. / decided not to deliver an opinion on the proposal. / The opinion of <u xml:id="_body_level_18_content_p_u_2">XXX</u> was requested on … (and is pending).
                    </p>
                </content>
            </level>
            <level xml:id="_body_level_19" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_19_num">19.</num>
                <content xml:id="_body_level_19_content">
                    <p xml:id="_body_level_19_content_p"><i xml:id="_body_level_19_content_p_i_1">(In case of a general approach)</i> On …, the <u xml:id="_body_level_19_content_p_u_1">Council</u> reached a general approach
                        <authorialNote xml:id="_authorialnote_8" marker="8" placement="bottom">
                            <p>12345/21.</p>
                        </authorialNote> on the abovementioned proposal, which constituted the mandate for negotiations with the European Parliament in the context of the ordinary legislative procedure.
                    </p>
                </content>
            </level>
            <level xml:id="_body_level_20" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_20_num">20.</num>
                <content xml:id="_body_level_20_content">
                    <p xml:id="_body_level_20_content_p"><i xml:id="_body_level_20_content_p_i_1">(In case of a Coreper-level mandate)</i> At its meeting on …,
                        the <u xml:id="_body_level_20_content_p_u_1">Permanent Representatives Committee</u> granted the … Presidency a mandate to enter into negotiations with the European Parliament.
                    </p>
                </content>
            </level>
            <level xml:id="_body_level_21" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_21_num">21.</num>
                <content xml:id="_body_level_21_content">
                    <p xml:id="_body_level_21_content_p">On …, a provisional agreement was reached between co-legislators, resulting in the final compromise text as set out in the annex/annexes (or in addendum/addenda XX) to this note.
                    </p>
                </content>
            </level>
            <division xml:id="_body_division_6" class="type_1">
                <num xml:id="_body_division_6_num"><b>VI.</b></num>
                <heading xml:id="_body_division_6_heading"><b>CONCLUSION</b></heading>
            </division>
            <level xml:id="_body_level_22" leos:depth="1">
                <num xml:id="_body_level_22_num">22.</num>
                <subparagraph xml:id="_body_level_22_subpara_1">
                    <content xml:id="_body_level_22_subpara_1_content">
                        <p xml:id="_body_level_22_content_p">The <u xml:id="_body_level_22_subpara_1_content__p_u_1">Permanent Representatives Committee</u> is therefore invited to:
                        </p>
                    </content>
                </subparagraph>
                <list xml:id="_body_level_22_list_1">
                    <point xml:id="_body_level_22_list_1_point_1">
                        <num xml:id="_body_level_22_list_1_point_1_num">(a)</num>
                        <content xml:id="_body_level_22_list_1_point_1_content">
                            <p xml:id="_body_level_22_list_1_point_1_content_p">confirm agreement on the final compromise text as set out in the annex/annexes (or in addendum/addenda
                                XX) to this note with a view to reaching an agreement at first reading with the European Parliament;
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </point>
                    <point xml:id="_body_level_22_list_1_point_2">
                        <num xml:id="_body_level_22_list_1_point_2_num">(b)</num>
                        <content xml:id="_body_level_22_list_1_point_2_content">
                            <p xml:id="_body_level_22_list_1_point_2_content_p">authorise the Chair of the Permanent Representatives Committee to send a letter to inform the Chair(s)
                                of the European Parliament’s … Committee(s) that, should the European Parliament adopt its position at first reading on the text of the proposal in
                                the exact form as set out in the annex/annexes (or in addendum/addenda XX) to this note, and subject to revision of that text by the lawyer-linguists
                                of both institutions, the Council will approve the European Parliament’s position and the act will be adopted in the wording which corresponds to the
                                European Parliament’s position.
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </point>
                </list>
            </level>
        </mainBody>
